  "prompt": "How can you see if someone deleted you on LINE?",
  "response": "On LINE, there isn't a direct way to see if someone has deleted you as a friend. However, there are a few signs you can look for that may indicate you've been removed:\n\n1. **Profile Visibility**: If you can no longer see the person\u2019s profile picture, status updates, or other information that was previously visible to you, it could mean they have deleted you.\n\n2. **Chat History**: If your chat history with that person is still accessible, but you can\u2019t send them messages (you get an error) or they are no longer appearing as a friend, this is a strong indication.\n\n3. **Previous Messages**: If you previously sent messages that the person hasn\u2019t seen (indicated by the double check marks) and those have turned to single check marks, it could mean you've been removed or blocked.\n\n4. **Search Function**: If you can't find them in the search function, this may indicate they have removed you, especially if they are set to \u2018Friends Only\u2019 in their privacy settings.\n\n5. **Trying to Add Again**: If you try to add them as a friend again and receive a notification that they are already on your friend list, but your chat history shows no messages, this may mean you've been removed.\n\nKeep in mind that these signs are not definitive proof. Someone might have adjusted their privacy settings or changed their account preferences without necessarily removing you. If you are unsure, the best approach is to communicate directly with the person.",
